cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about response selection in retrieval-based chatbots, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and conversational agents. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new architecture that uses neural networks, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning) as likely sub-categories. The paper involves matching and ranking responses, which suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses a recurrent neural network to model relationships among utterances, which suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible sub-category.
